main event: A bright yellow object was observed moving rapidly from east to west over Presque Isle, Maine on July 30, 1956.
interesting points: The object made a right-angle turn and retraced its path.
The object was covered by a thin, bright cloud cover.
Similar sightings of a 'mystery fireball' were reported in the North Wilmington area of New Hampshire on July 31, 1956.
The case was concluded to be a sighting of the planet Venus passing in and out of a thin cloud cover.
